'''BahÃ­a Solano''' is a municipality and town in the [[ChocÃ³ Department]], [[Colombia]]. Bahia, as it is locally known, is an economic and touristic{{Lopsided|date=June 2011}} center of coastal Choco. Bahia is home to an airport as well as seaport, and along with daily flights to and from Medellin, Quibdo, Cali, and Bogota, there are bi-weekly ships that take passengers and cargo from Bahia to the port of Buenaventura. The region around Bahia Solano is home to world class{{Lopsided|date=June 2011}} scuba diving and sport fishing, providing a plethora of marine activities to the traveller. Only 18km away from Bahia Solano, is the stunning{{Lopsided|date=June 2011}} beach town of [[El Valle, Choco]]. It's beaches, rivers, waterfalls, and cultural diversity{{Lopsided|date=June 2011}} are but some of the attractions that make this village a must see{{Lopsided|date=June 2011}} on any Colombian travel list. El Valle's Almejal Beach is gaining the reputation{{Lopsided|date=June 2011}} as one of the premier surf breaks in Colombia. In addition, El Valle is the closest community to Ensenada de Utria National Park, located only 9km down the beach. [[File:Flag of BahÃ­a Solano, ChocÃ³.svg|thumb|right|Flag of BahÃ­a Solano]]â
